race.comment: IMPENDING WAR (2) was well fancied to win when returing a gelding at Werribee so backers there will have walked away underwhelmed. It was a tricky enough spot against the older horses and not particularly well weighted. Looks a much better scenario now second up at the 1400m and back against his own age group with the claim for an apprentice who can ride plenty of winners over the summer. DAVIDA (11) was pitched into listed company fresh. No match there but she is far better suited this time and thinking she runs a good race. SIGNORETTI (8) continues to front up and race well with ratings that are in the game against these. Much tougher for TOY QUEEN (10) but she went about it the right way winning her maiden from the front at Mornington. BUCCLEUCH (1) had the better of IMPENDING WAR and looked smart over the winter. Nice base at the trials and too good to ignore entirely here - though suspicion is that he will be much better next time.
